+-        "# Topology Consistency Analysis\n",
+-        "## Purpose\n",
+-        "Identify which specific spline connections survive across all 10\n",
+-        "independent seeds per condition after training is complete.\n",
+-        "Measure how consistent the surviving topology is across seeds\n",
+-        "and test whether surviving connections correspond to physically\n",
+-        "meaningful state variables.\n",
+-        "\n",
+-        "## The Central Experiment\n",
+-        "For HalfCheetah-v4: test pre-registered prediction that back thigh\n",
+-        "and back shin splines survive while foot splines go flat, consistent\n",
+-        "with biomechanical analysis of 2D locomotion.\n",
+-        "For Hopper-v4: test pre-registered prediction that hip and thigh\n",
+-        "splines survive while foot splines contribute less.\n",
+-        "\n",
+-        "## Why This Matters\n",
+-        "If the same splines die across 9 or 10 out of 10 independent seeds\n",
+-        "despite different random initializations, the sparsity pattern\n",
+-        "reflects something real about the environment physics rather than\n",
+-        "training noise. This is supporting evidence for the central claim\n",
+-        "that emergent sparsity captures genuine causal structure.\n",
+-        "\n",
+-        "## Outputs\n",
+-        "- Topology consistency heatmap: which connections survived across\n",
+-        "  all seeds, visualized as a grid\n",
+-        "- Consistency score per connection: fraction of seeds in which\n",
+-        "  each spline remained active\n",
+-        "- Comparison against pre-registered predictions\n",
+-        "- Classical control theory / biomechanics annotation of each\n",
+-        "  surviving connection explaining why it makes physical sense\n",
+-        "\n",
+-        "## This Is Experiment 2 Of 4\n",
+-        "Results from this notebook feed directly into the robustness\n",
+-        "correlation analysis in 07_robustness_testing.ipynb\n",
+-        "\n",
